# Pass C: Grammar Function Harvest Prompt
# Use ONLY for function words (article, pronoun, particle, conjunction, preposition, etc.).
# If lemma is a content word (noun, verb, adjective, numeral), return empty shell JSON.

Lemma: {{lemma}}
Part of Speech (from base/external): {{partOfSpeech}}
Base JSON:
{{base_json}}
External JSON:
{{external_json}}

## FUNCTION WORD DETECTION
Treat as function word if partOfSpeech (case-insensitive) matches any:
article, pronoun, personal pronoun, reflexive pronoun, intensive pronoun, demonstrative, relative pronoun, interrogative, indefinite pronoun, particle, conjunction, preposition, adverb, determiner, enclitic.
Else: output minimal JSON:
{ "lemma": "{{lemma}}", "functions": [], "notes": ["Skipped (content word)"], "warnings": [] }

## TASK (when function word)
Harvest Hellenistic (300 BCE–300 CE) discourse / syntactic functions from grammars:
Sources (public-domain quoting allowed in short clauses):
- BDF (Blass-Debrunner-Funk)
- MHT (Moulton-Howard-Turner)
- Robertson
- Mayser
- Gignac
- Smyth
- Runge (paraphrase; modern copyright) -> paraphrase: true
- Levinsohn (paraphrase: true)

Do NOT:
- Create senses.
- Promote historical demonstrative for ὁ or αὐτός (mark nonProductive).
- Invent examples; only use established, widely attested Hellenistic forms.
- Quote restricted sources verbatim.

## OUTPUT SCHEMA
{
  "lemma": "string",
  "functions": [
    {
      "label": "string",            // e.g. "Emphatic self-reference"
      "description": "string",      // concise (≤ 160 chars)
      "example": "string|null",     // Greek minimal phrase
      "translation": "string|null", // idiomatic English
      "source": "string",           // BDF, MHT, Robertson, Mayser, Gignac, Smyth, Runge(paraphrase), Levinsohn(paraphrase)
      "ref": "string|null",         // e.g. "Luke 5:37", "BDF §252"
      "paraphrase": true|false,
      "nonProductive": true|false   // historical / not productive
    }
  ],
  "structuralPatterns": [
    {
      "pattern": "string",          // e.g. "article + adjective + noun"
      "example": "string|null",
      "translation": "string|null",
      "note": "string|null",
      "nonProductive": true|false
    }
  ],
  "notes": [ "string" ],
  "warnings": [ "string" ]
}

## FUNCTION TYPES TO SEEK (IF APPLICABLE)
- Emphasis / Intensification (αὐτός)
- Anaphoric / Cataphoric referencing
- Contrast / Topic shift (e.g., article + δέ cycles; μέν … δέ)
- Focus / Framing (particles)
- Clause linkage (logical: inference, concession, condition)
- Nominalization (article + participle / infinitive)
- Distributive structures (ὁ μὲν … ὁ δέ)
- Equative / sameness pattern (τὸ αὐτό)
- Preposition semantic extensions (spatial → metaphorical)
- Aspectual / scalar particle functions
- Negative reinforcement (οὐ …, μή with particles)
- Structural patterns (double article, repeated particle clusters)

## RULES
- Max functions: 18
- Max structuralPatterns: 8
- Keep descriptions plain English.
- Example must be Hellenistic; if uncertain, omit.
- For ὁ / αὐτός: add note "Historical demonstrative use not productive in Koiné."

## VALIDATION (INTERNAL—DO NOT OUTPUT)
[ ] No invented refs
[ ] Dates implicitly Hellenistic
[ ] nonProductive flagged where historical only
[ ] paraphrase true for Runge / Levinsohn
[ ] No "Demonstrative Pronoun" function for ὁ / αὐτός

## OUTPUT
Return ONLY the JSON object.
If not function word → minimal JSON as specified above.